f=Engineering/mia/custom/ui-accessibility-standards/SKILL.md · in=ui-accessibility-standards mia builds interfaces consistent, usable, accessible: components built design tokens, semantic HTML, keyboard operability, WCAG-conformant contrast/labels/focus product works everyone looks like one product, patchwork. Accessibility later pass; it's components built. · p=Two failure modes prevents: inconsistency (every screen slightly different button, spacing, interaction) inaccessibility (unusable keyboard, invisible screen readers, failing contrast excluding users and, increasingly, failing legal requirements). come building screens hoc instead component system accessibility baked in. · wu=Triggers: "build component/screen," "is accessible," "a11y," "WCAG," "keyboard navigation," "contrast," "the inconsistent," any user-facing interface work. · st:/ Protocol=`A UI to build \· -> COMPONENTS from the system: reuse before creating; new components enter the library, tokens-based \· -> SEMANTIC HTML: the right element (button is a <button>), not a div with a click handler \· -> KEYBOARD: everything operable without a mouse; visible focus; logical tab order \· -> SCREEN READERS: labels, roles, alt text, ARIA only where semantics fall short` · in=**Build component system.** Reuse existing component before creating one; genuinely new component enters shared library, built design tokens. hoc one-off components consistency dies (and agent-generated sprawls dev's integrity concern). **Semantic HTML first.** correct element carries accessibility free `<button>` focusable, keyboard-activatable, announced button; `<div onclick>` none reimplement (usually incompletely). ARIA patch semantics genuinely fall short, substitute them. **Keyboard-operable, always.** interaction works without mouse: focusable controls, visible focus indicators, logical tab order, keyboard traps. accessibility requirement correctness one (many bugs hide mouse-only paths). **Screen-reader support.** Meaningful labels, correct roles, alt text informative images (empty alt decorative), form fields associated labels. Test accessibility tree, visual. **WCAG contrast sizing.** Text meets contrast (design-tokens already encode compliant color pairings token pairing fails contrast, that's kit/token finding atlas). Touch targets adequately sized; text resizable. **Verify real browser.** Accessibility consistency claims checked real rendering (frontend-verification's Agentation loop quinn's Reticle/Playwright), asserted "it's accessible" without check "agents say done" problem, a11y edition. · of=`## UI: [component/screen] \· Components: [reused / new → library, tokens-based] \· Semantic HTML: [correct elements ✓] \· Keyboard: [operable ✓ \· visible focus ✓ \· logical order ✓] \· Screen reader: [labels/roles/alt ✓] \· Contrast/sizing: [WCAG AA ✓ / token pairing fails → atlas finding] \· Verified in browser: [frontend-verification ref]` · pr=**Build component system** reuse first; new components join library, tokens-based., **Semantic HTML first** right element gives accessibility free; ARIA patches, never substitutes., **Keyboard-operable always** mouse-only paths; visible focus; traps., **Screen-reader support built in** labels, roles, alt; test accessibility tree., **WCAG contrast/sizing** token pairings encode it; failing pairing atlas finding., **Verified real browser** accessibility checked, claimed. · f=component library start one first components (tokens-based, accessible); don't build screens one-offs library later reconcile., Component library stack lacks accessibility wrap/fix adoption flag upstream; don't inherit inaccessibility silently., Design mockup fails contrast flag atlas (the token/kit source), don't ship failing pairing "match design"; design bug. · b:with Other Skills=**design-tokens** (sibling): components built tokens; contrast compliance lives token pairings (atlas)., **frontend-verification** (sibling): real-browser check accessibility consistency (Agentation Reticle/Playwright)., **frontend-performance** (sibling): accessible fast aren't tension; built., **atlas lena (Brand Studio)**: visual voice consistency; contrast-failing brand pairing atlas's resolve., **raj**: components consume raj's API contracts; loading/error/empty states part accessible UI., **quinn**: browser-verified accessibility gate evidence.